## Accessibility

### Reduced Motion
Always respect user preferences:

```css
@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
  * {
    animation-duration: 0.01ms !important;
    transition-duration: 0.01ms !important;
  }
}
```

### Focus States
Always provide visible focus indicators:

```css
.btn:focus-visible {
  outline: 2px solid var(--accent);
  outline-offset: 2px;
}
```

### Color Contrast
- Ensure text meets WCAG AA standards (4.5:1 for normal text)
- Use `--ink` for primary text on `--bg`
- Use `--ink-dim` or `--muted` for secondary text

## Brand-Specific Overrides

Use the `data-brand` attribute for conditional styling:

```css
/* Asteria (default) */
.headline {
  font-weight: 600;
  color: var(--ink);
}

/* Cosmo variant */
[data-brand='cosmo'] .headline {
  font-weight: 800;
  background: linear-gradient(90deg, var(--accent1), var(--accent2), var(--accent3));
  -webkit-background-clip: text;
  color: transparent;
}
```

## Performance

### Efficient Selectors
- Avoid deep nesting (max 3 levels)
- Use class selectors over element selectors
- Minimize use of universal selector (`*`)

### CSS Variables
- Use CSS variables for theming
- Avoid inline styles; use classes instead
- Leverage cascade and inheritance

## Glass Morphism (Asteria Only)
```css
.glass-panel {
  background: var(--glass);
  backdrop-filter: blur(20px);
  border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.12);
  border-radius: var(--radius);
}
```

## Animations
- Keep animations under 400ms for snappy feel
- Use `transform` and `opacity` for GPU acceleration
- Always provide fallbacks for reduced motion
- See [animation-gsap.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/animation-gsap.mdc) for GSAP guidelines
